$ Microsoft Office Visual Basic Editor: Immediate Window
@ immediate window

The *immediate window* (German: *Direktbereich*) is located in the → Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor[Visual Basic editor]. In the Visual Basic editor, the immediate window
can be opened by pressing `Ctrl-G`.

{ Insert a line

  By default, pressing `enter` tries to execute the command that is stored in the line on which the cursor is positioned.

  In order to prevent such an execution and add a line, `ctrl+enter` must be used.


}

sa:
  In order to dock the Immedate Window to the bottom after undocking it, → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/VBA/7_0/Common#reg-dock-vb-editor[the registry must be manipulated].
